HEADWORD: Hagioscope
<hw>Ha"gi*o*scope`</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧"j⟦icr⟧*⟦osl⟧*sk⟦omac⟧p`)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>"a`gios</grk> sacred +
<ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <def>An opening made in the interior walls of
a cruciform church to afford a view of the altar to those in the
transepts; -- called, in architecture, a <xex>squint</xex>.</def>
<rj><au>Hook.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

